      • SnmpTrapRecipient

        @Since(value="7.0")
public SnmpTrapRecipient(String host,
                       String community,
                       Long port)
        Host that is to receive the traps generated by the cluster.
        Parameters:
        host - [required] The IP address or host name of the target network management station.
        community - [required] SNMP community string.
        port - [required] The UDP port number on the host where the trap is to be sent. Valid range is 1 - 65535. 0 (zero) is not a valid port number. Default is 162.
        Since:
        7.0
